Authority of the Department of Petroleum Resources in Katsina state, has closed down A U Sauki filing station and arrested the owner for selling fuel inside polythene bags. The state Controller, Aminu Mohammed, who told pressmen during the operation in the Katsina, said “we are on a normal monitoring operation round the town and we discovered the station selling fuel in a polythene bags which is inappropriate. “We decided to seal off the station and arrest the owner, he is going to face the full wrath of the law. We have been doing this operation for quite some time, the owner of the station will attest to the fact that we were here sometimes back to warn them, but today we’ve decided to close down the station and we will prosecute him to serve as a deterrent to others.” The Commandant, Nigeria Security and Civil Defense Corp (NSCDC) in the state, Nzomosel Moses, said the Corp is working hand in hand with DPR in apprehending offenders and then charge them to court for prosecution, adding that the command would continue to collaborate with DPR in tracking down illegal operators of Petro substances in as much as people refuse to do the right thing in the state.